                <p xml:id="KR1j0018-start">
                    <seg corresp="#KR1j0018_tls_001-p0025a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-20T06:11:06.929+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1j0018_tls_001-p0025a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-16T23:50:36.421+09:00">“於悉切：本书反切是徐铉采用孙愐《唐韵》的音。” TKJ 2020</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1j0018_tls_001-p0027a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-16T23:52:19.801+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1j0018_tls_001-p0028a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-16T23:58:19.175+09:00">“丕，大。从一，不声。”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1j0018_tls_001-p0029a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-17T00:02:31.815+09:00">“吏的本义是“治理人的人”，即古代官吏的通称。《孟子·公孙丑上》：“无敌于天下者，天吏也。”在天下没有匹敌的人，是奉行天命的官吏。《左传·成公二年》：“王使委于三吏。”周定王叫他把战利品交给三公。杜预注：“三吏，三公也。”可见君、相皆可称吏。汉以后特指官府的小官和差役。”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1j0018_tls_001-p0029a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-17T00:05:03.603+09:00">This nicely illustrates Xu Kai's semantically more speculative approach. No wonder that Qiu Xigui xiansheng prefers 大徐本 so emphatically, at all times.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1j0018_tls_001-p7175a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-19T22:23:20.205+09:00">The gloss 專壹 is highly relevant: 壹 is a different word used  by the 公孫鞅 to mean "be ideologically united and well-focussed" 許慎 treats 壹 and 一　as writing two different homophonous words.</seg>
                </p>
